{"word":"ἅλας","slug":"ἅλας","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἅλας, ατος, τό</el></b> [= <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὁ\">ὁ</a> ἅλς</el> ‘salt’; <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ s.\">s.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἁλιεύς\">ἁλιεύς</a></el>] <b><i>salt</i> <a href='B:470 5:13'>Mt 5:13b</a>; <a href='B:490 14:34'>Lk 14:34</a>;</b> extended to witty or winsome speech<b> <a href='B:580 4:6'>Col 4:6</a>;</b> also applied to a favorable impression made on one’s society through arousal of positive interest <b><a href='B:470 5:13'>Mt 5:13a</a>.</b> The older form <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἅλα\">ἅλα</a></el> occurs <b><a href='B:480 9:50'>Mk 9:50</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a></b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἄλαλος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἁλεεῖς\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}